<br>
--- Original Message -----<br>
From: &quot;Ben Pearson&quot; &lt;tuvas@email.arizona.edu&gt;<br>
To: &quot;William Mook&quot; &lt;Stuff@stuff.com&gt; (Again, real email changed)<br>
Sent: Tuesday, October 22, 2002 10:13 PM<br>
Subject: RE: A new look at nuclear pulse<br>
<br>
<br>
&gt; Wow, so much for a few points... Hmmm.<br>
<br>
Sorry. It comes from typing 180 wpm.<br>
<br>
&gt; 1)The radiation figures I used were not my own, I used information from<br>
the<br>
&gt; Project Orion book by George Dyson.<br>
<br>
Yes. I read that book. They didn't provide the physical data behind the<br>
result either. But there is a bibliography!<br>
<br>
&gt; That was not my focus. I only had very<br>
&gt; limited time to work on this, there's only so much I can do. I mean, I'm<br>
&gt; an undergrad engineering student, this was just a hobby.<br>
<br>
Yes. And, then there's one's social life! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&gt; 2)I have absolutely no distinguishment between HEMP and secondary EMP<br>
effects,<br>
<br>
That's what I thought.<br>
<br>
&gt; remember, I'm not a nuclear physist. Besides, for my calculations, they<br>
weren't<br>
&gt; really that important.<br>
<br>
Well, if you believe you'll get wide area EMP, its important to understand<br>
the basic physics behind what's going on when that happens. Two results are<br>
obvious to any physicist; (1) its incredibly easy to knock out power grids<br>
and such with the right kind of blast; (2) its incredibly easy to reduce or<br>
eliminate EMP effects altogether, again with the right kind of blast. This<br>
means, while EMP effects are an importation consideration, they're not a<br>
show stopper. Its sort of like pronation or exhaust systems on your car.<br>
Details that are important for safety and comfort, but details to be worked<br>
out, not show stoppers.<br>
<br>
&gt; Your ideas may work.<br>
<br>
Yes. I wasn't looking for approval, but yes. They will.<br>
<br>
&gt; Reading them I can't tell if they are original to you<br>
&gt; or copied,<br>
<br>
